					<head>Commentary</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597" rend="visible">
						<summary>The book of Isaiah: the Hebrew text written in Arabic characters, with an Arabic translation and a commentary of Japhet ben Ali.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="ar">Hebrew, Arabic</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
							<locus from="1r" to="187v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush Yesha῾yahu</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרוש ישעיהו </title>
							<note>
								<p>Contains the pointed and accentuated biblical text in Arabic characters, accompanied by an Arabic translation and a commentary.</p>
								<p>A number of masoretic notes.</p>
								<p>The diacritic points are generally added.</p>
								<p>Follows a simple phonetic method of transcription.</p>
							</note>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961">Japhet ben Ali, ha-Levi,‏ active 10th century</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961">יפת בן עלי, הלוי</persName>
							</author>
							<filiation>Cf. a similar handwriting in <ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">301</ref>, which is dated <date calendar="Gregorian">1004-1005</date>.</filiation>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex, a Naskhi hand of approximately 11th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex</support>
								<extent>187 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>233</height>
										<width>173</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>162</height>
										<width>140</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>187 folios (+ 2 paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Originally consisting of two parts, each having its quires separately numbered.</p>
									<p>Part 1 is now represented by folios 1-12. Part two consists currently of folios 13-185.</p>
									<p>Substantial lacunae after folios: 1, 7, 8, 10, 11, 12, 14, 16, 26, 36, 37, 39, 88, 96, 137, 139, 141, 143, 149, 153, 155, 157, 159, 165, 175.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Several of the extant folios have been more or less damaged.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="11 13" writtenLines="11 13">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>A Naskhi hand of approximately 11th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Arabic" scope="major"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folios 186r-187v: two appended leaves, consisting of the Hebrew text in Arabic transcription of Isaiah 26:15-27:13. The Hebrew vowel-point and accents are added in red ink. Cf. <ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">278</ref>, folios 288r-290v.</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>BM in-house.</p>
								<p>Spine: 'Isaiah. Yefet's Comm. Hebrew &amp; Arabic. Brit. Mus. Oriental 2548.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
